      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start, but it feels a bit too \"standard.\" For the part about why market mechanisms can't fix it, can you help me write a paragraph that really hammers home why the \"meritocracy\" argument used by critics is basically just a way to ignore historical theft and systemic racism? I want to frame their view as something that's not just wrong, but fundamentally harmful to progress.",
