      "content": "The concept of \"meritocracy\" is a dangerous myth that conveniently erases the foundational theft and systemic barriers faced by marginalized communities. Critics who cling to this idea willfully ignore centuries of discriminatory practices, from slavery to redlining, which actively rigged the economic game before anyone even started playing. To accept meritocracy is to endorse a narrative that blames the victim for the structural violence inflicted upon them, thereby protecting the entrenched privileges of the wealthy.",
